    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-24T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-24T09:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2131/284: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-24T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 24, 1935—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Your telegram No. 3, January 23, 6 p.m. Does my telegram No. 11, January 23,
                    6 p.m., affect the instruction that I see the Foreign <pb facs="0526" n="433"
                        xml:id="pg_433"/> Minister? There appears to be no likelihood of an early
                    adjournment of Congress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
